}\!-\!10^{8.3} \,{\rm M}\_{\odot }$</tex-math></inline-formula>. Our new candidates improve the completeness of the QSO sample at <inline-formula><tex-math id=``TM0008'' notation=``LaTeX''>$z=0.8\!-\!1.6$</tex- math></inline-formula> in the 3D-HST field. The proposed method will also be helpful for QSO selections via slitless spectroscopy in Euclid and the Chinese Space Station Telescope.}},
    doi = {10.1093/mnras/staf849},
